summary:
The Security Council, 
Taking note of the IAEA report on the Implementation of the NPT Safeguards Agreement, 
Reaffirming commitment to the Treaty on Non-Proliferation of Nuclear Weapons (NPT), 
1. Reaffirms previous resolutions and statements (S/PRST/2006/15, 1696 (2006), 1737 (2006), 1747 (2007), and 1803 (2008)); 
2. Takes note of the 3 March 2008 Statement by Foreign Ministers on a dual-track approach to the Iranian nuclear issue; 
3. Reaffirms commitment to an early negotiated solution to the Iranian nuclear issue; 
4. Calls upon Iran to comply fully and without delay with its obligations under mentioned resolutions and IAEA requirements; 
5. Decides to remain seized of the matter.
